Package neureka.ndim.config

Class AbstractNDC

java.lang.Object
neureka.ndim.config.AbstractNDC
All Implemented Interfaces:
NDConfiguration
Direct Known Subclasses:
D1C, D2C, D3C, PermutedNDConfiguration, Simple0DConfiguration, SimpleNDConfiguration, SimpleReshapeView, Sliced0DConfiguration, SlicedNDConfiguration, VirtualNDConfiguration
public abstract class AbstractNDC extends Object implements NDConfiguration
The following is an abstract implementation of the NDConfiguration which offers a basis for instantiation and caching of concrete implementations extending this abstract class. Concrete NDConfiguration implementations are expected to be immutable which ensures that sharing them is safe. In order to cash instances based in their field variables, this class comes with a common implementation of the NDConfiguration.hashCode() method. NDConfiguration implementation instances will be used by tensors which often times share the same shape, and way of mapping indices to their respective data. In these cases tensors can simply share their NDConfiguration instances for memory efficiency.

      protected static int[] _cacheArray(int[] data)
      This method receives an int array and returns an int array which can either be the one provided or an array found in the global int array cache residing inside this class. Integer array based configurations are not very large, that is why their state can uniquely be encoded in long keys.
      Parameters:
      data - The integer array which ought to be cached.
      Returns:
      The provided array or an already present array found in the int array cache.
